cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely category as answer set programming is a popular paradigm for declarative problem solving in AI. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also likely as the paper discusses the translation of answer-set programs into logic. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses the syntax and formalization of problems as rule sets. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of SMT solvers for problem solving. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper reports on experimental results and performance comparisons.
